Gotthard Base Tunnel.label: Gotthard Base Tunnel
Gotthard Base Tunnel.description: The Gotthard Base Tunnel is a railway tunnel in the heart of the Swiss Alps expected to open in 2016. Wikipedia

Seikan Tunnel.label: Seikan Tunnel
Seikan Tunnel.description: The Seikan Tunnel is a 53.85-kilometre railway tunnel in Japan, with a 23.3-kilometre long portion under the seabed. The track level is about 140 metres below the seabed and 240 m below sea level. Wikipedia
Address: 〒030-1501 青森県東津軽郡今別町浜名字黒崎

Aylsham Bypass Tunnel.label: Aylsham Bypass Tunnel
Aylsham Bypass Tunnel.description: The Aylsham Bypass Tunnel is the only railway tunnel in Norfolk, England currently open to trains. It carries the narrow gauge Bure Valley Railway under the Aylsham Bypass. Wikipedia

Center City Commuter Connection.label: Center City Commuter Connection
Center City Commuter Connection.description: The Center City Commuter Connection, commonly referred to as "the commuter tunnel", is a passenger railroad tunnel in Center City, Philadelphia, Pennsylvania, United States, built to connect the stub ... Wikipedia

Michigan Central Railway Tunnel.label: Michigan Central Railway Tunnel
Michigan Central Railway Tunnel.description: The Michigan Central Railway Tunnel is a railroad tunnel under the Detroit River connecting Detroit, Michigan, in the United States with Windsor, Ontario, in Canada. The US entrance is south of Porter and Vermont streets near Rosa Parks Boulevard. Wikipedia

Robertson Tunnel.label: Robertson Tunnel
Robertson Tunnel.description: The Robertson Tunnel is a twin-bore light rail tunnel through the Tualatin Mountains west of Portland, Oregon, used by the MAX Blue and Red Lines. The tunnel is 2.9 miles long and consists of twin 21-foot-diameter tunnels. Wikipedia

Box Tunnel.label: Box Tunnel
Box Tunnel.description: Box Tunnel is a railway tunnel in Western England, between Bath and Chippenham, dug through Box Hill, and is one of the most significant structures on the Great Western Main Line. Wikipedia

Berkeley Hills Tunnel.label: Berkeley Hills Tunnel
Berkeley Hills Tunnel.description: The Berkeley Hills Tunnel is a tunnel which carries Bay Area Rapid Transit's Pittsburg/Bay Point–SFO/Millbrae line through the Berkeley Hills between the Rockridge and Orinda stations. Wikipedia

Blue Ridge Tunnel.label: Blue Ridge Tunnel
Blue Ridge Tunnel.description: The Blue Ridge Tunnel is a historic railroad tunnel built during the construction of the Blue Ridge Railroad in the 1850s. Wikipedia

Bradway Tunnel.label: Bradway Tunnel
Bradway Tunnel.description: Bradway Tunnel, 2,027 yards long, was built in 1870 about 1-mile north of Dronfield, Derbyshire, in South Yorkshire, England. Wikipedia

Sunset Tunnel.label: Sunset Tunnel
Sunset Tunnel.description: The Sunset Tunnel is a 4,232 ft-long light rail/streetcar tunnel in San Francisco, California. The tunnel runs under the steep hill that Buena Vista Park is located on and is used by the N Judah Muni Metro line. Wikipedia

Twin Peaks Tunnel.label: Twin Peaks Tunnel
Twin Peaks Tunnel.description: The Twin Peaks Tunnel is a 2.27-mile-long light rail/streetcar tunnel in San Francisco, California. The tunnel runs under the Twin Peaks and is used by the K Ingleside, L Taraval, M Ocean View, and T Third Street Muni Metro lines. Wikipedia

Albula Tunnel.label: Albula Tunnel
Albula Tunnel.description: The Albula Tunnel is the centrepiece of the Albula Railway, which forms part of the Rhaetian Railway network, in the Canton of Graubünden, Switzerland. Wikipedia

Perthus Tunnel.label: Perthus Tunnel
Perthus Tunnel.description: The Perthus Tunnel is a twin-bore railway tunnel between Perpignan, France and Figueres, Spain built as part of the high-speed railway line between Barcelona and Montpellier under the Eastern Pyrenees. Wikipedia

Kilsby Tunnel.label: Kilsby Tunnel
Kilsby Tunnel.description: The Kilsby Tunnel is a railway tunnel on the West Coast Main Line railway in England. It was designed and engineered by Robert Stephenson. Wikipedia

Marmaray.label: Marmaray
Marmaray.description: Marmaray is a rail transport project in the Turkish city of Istanbul. It comprises an undersea rail tunnel under the Bosphorus strait, and the modernization of existing suburban railway lines along the ... Wikipedia

Channel Tunnel.label: Channel Tunnel
Channel Tunnel.description: The Channel Tunnel is a 50.5-kilometre rail tunnel linking Folkestone, Kent, in the United Kingdom, with Coquelles, Pas-de-Calais, near Calais in northern France, beneath the English Channel at the Strait of Dover. Wikipedia

Jarlsberg Tunnel.label: Jarlsberg Tunnel
Jarlsberg Tunnel.description: The Jarlsberg Tunnel is a 1,750-meter long double track railway tunnel which runs through Frodeåsen in Tønsberg, Norway. Wikipedia

Perkasie Tunnel.label: Perkasie Tunnel
Perkasie Tunnel.description: The Perkasie Tunnel is a train tunnel located behind the Post Office in Perkasie, Pennsylvania on 7th Street, on a line owned by SEPTA and operated by the East Penn Railroad. The tunnel itself is located near 8th Street and Ridge Road. Wikipedia

Skaugum Tunnel.label: Skaugum Tunnel
Skaugum Tunnel.description: The Skaugum Tunnel is a 3,790-meter long railway tunnel in Asker, Norway, on the Asker Line. The tunnel runs between Asker Station and Solstad and was built as part of the first stage of the Asker Line, between Asker and Sandvika. Wikipedia

Brenner Base Tunnel.label: Brenner Base Tunnel
Brenner Base Tunnel.description: The Brenner Base Tunnel is a planned 55-kilometre long railway tunnel through the base of the Brenner massif. It will run from Innsbruck Hauptbahnhof in Austria to Franzensfeste in Italy, replacing part of the current Brenner railway. Wikipedia

Furka Summit Tunnel.label: Furka Summit Tunnel
Furka Summit Tunnel.description: The Furka Summit Tunnel is a 1,874 metres long railway tunnel in southern Switzerland. It lies at an altitude of 2,160 metres. The summit tunnel was completed in 1925, and first opened on 3 July 1926. Wikipedia

Transbay Tube.label: Transbay Tube
Transbay Tube.description: The Transbay Tube is an underwater rail tunnel which carries Bay Area Rapid Transit's four transbay lines under San Francisco Bay between the cities of San Francisco and Oakland in California. Wikipedia

Kvineshei Tunnel.label: Kvineshei Tunnel
Kvineshei Tunnel.description: Kvineshei Tunnel is the fourth longest railway tunnel in Norway and located between Snartemo Station and Kvinesdal on Sørlandsbanen. It was opened in 1943 when Sørlandsbanen was extended to Moi. Wikipedia

Castle Shannon Incline.label: Castle Shannon Incline
Castle Shannon Incline.description: The Castle Shannon Incline was a funicular railroad in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania. It was originally built in 1890 as part of the Pittsburgh and Castle Shannon Railroad as a means of transporting passenger ... Wikipedia

Colwall Tunnels.label: Colwall Tunnels
Colwall Tunnels.description: The Colwall Tunnels are a pair of railway tunnels that connect Colwall and Malvern Wells on the Cotswold Line, passing under the Malvern Hills in the Welsh Marches region of England. Wikipedia

Conococheague Mountain Tunnel.label: Conococheague Mountain Tunnel
Conococheague Mountain Tunnel.description: The Conococheague Mountain Tunnel was a proposed railroad tunnel in Perry County, Pennsylvania. It was originally planned as part of the Path Valley Railroad, with the intent to link the Newport and ... Wikipedia

Hægebostad Tunnel.label: Hægebostad Tunnel
Hægebostad Tunnel.description: Hægebostad Tunnel is the fifth longest railway tunnel in Norway and located between Audnedal Station and Snartemo Station on Sørlandsbanen. It was opened in 1943 when Sørlandsbanen was extended to Moi. Wikipedia

Ledbury Tunnel.label: Ledbury Tunnel
Ledbury Tunnel.description: Ledbury Tunnel is a single-track railway tunnel immediately to the east of Ledbury railway station on the Cotswold Line, in Herefordshire, England. Wikipedia

City Tunnel (Malmö).label: City Tunnel
City Tunnel (Malmö).description: The City Tunnel is a 17-kilometre rail link in Malmö, Sweden, running between Malmö Central Station and the Öresund Line, of which six kilometres under Malmö city centre is in tunnel, to increase ... Wikipedia

Ōhikage Tunnel.label: Ōhikage Tunnel
Ōhikage Tunnel.description: The Ōhikage Tunnel is a preserved railway tunnel located near Katsunuma-budōkyō on the Chūō Main Line in Kōshū, Yamanashi Prefecture, Japan. Wikipedia

Negro Mountain Tunnel.label: Negro Mountain Tunnel
Negro Mountain Tunnel.description: The Negro Mountain Tunnel is a tunnel located in Negro Mountain in Somerset County, Pennsylvania. It was built by New York Central Railroad as part of the proposed but never completed South Pennsylvania ... Wikipedia

Västlänken.label: Western Link
Västlänken.description: Västlänken is a planned railway tunnel under central Gothenburg. The purpose of the project is to increase capacity and reduce travel times on the Gothenburg network by changing the Gothenburg Central ... Wikipedia

Brush Tunnel.label: Brush Tunnel
Brush Tunnel.description:
Brush Tunnel is a 914-foot railroad tunnel located about 1 mile west of Corriganville, Maryland.
It was built in 1911 by the Western Maryland Railway, and is currently used by the Western Maryland Scenic ... Wikipedia

Cross-Harbour Tunnel.label: Cross-Harbour Tunnel
Cross-Harbour Tunnel.description: The Cross-Harbour Tunnel is the first tunnel in Hong Kong built underwater. It is two steel road tunnels each with two lanes constructed using the single shell immersed tube method. Wikipedia

Indigo Tunnel.label: Indigo Tunnel
Indigo Tunnel.description: Indigo Tunnel is an abandoned railroad tunnel in Allegany County, Maryland, located about 1 mile east of Little Orleans. Built by the Western Maryland Railway in 1904, Indigo was the company's longest tunnel. Wikipedia

Rimutaka Tunnel.label: Rimutaka Tunnel
Rimutaka Tunnel.description:
The Rimutaka Tunnel is a railway tunnel through New Zealand's Rimutaka Ranges, between Maymorn, near Upper Hutt, and Featherston, on the Wairarapa Line.
The tunnel, which was opened to traffic on 3 November 1955, is 8.798 kilometres long. Wikipedia

Romerike Tunnel.label: Romerike Tunnel
Romerike Tunnel.description: The Romerike Tunnel is a 14.580-kilometre railway tunnel in Norway that connects Oslo with Lillestrøm. Being the longest railway tunnel in Norway, the tunnel forms the first half of the Gardermoen Line. Wikipedia

Uptown Hudson Tubes.label: Uptown Hudson Tubes
Uptown Hudson Tubes.description: The Uptown Hudson Tubes are a pair of tunnels that carry PATH trains under the Hudson River between New York City and Jersey City, New Jersey. Wikipedia

Big Savage Tunnel.label: Big Savage Tunnel
Big Savage Tunnel.description: The Big Savage Tunnel is an abandoned railway tunnel located about 9 miles southeast of Meyersdale, Pennsylvania. The Big Savage, Borden Tunnel, and Brush Tunnels are part of the Great Allegheny Passage rail trail. Wikipedia

Borden Tunnel.label: Borden Tunnel
Borden Tunnel.description: The Borden Tunnel is a 957-foot formerly abandoned railway tunnel located about 2.5 miles north of Frostburg, Maryland. Unlighted, it is now part of the Great Allegheny Passage rail trail. Wikipedia

Flat Rock Tunnel.label: Flat Rock Tunnel
Flat Rock Tunnel.description: The Flat Rock Tunnel is an active railroad tunnel located on Norfolk Southern's Harrisburg Line near Manayunk, Pennsylvania, USA. The tunnel was built by the Reading Railroad for its line along the Schuylkill River. Wikipedia

Kessler Tunnel.label: Kessler Tunnel
Kessler Tunnel.description: Kessler Tunnel is an abandoned railroad tunnel in Allegany County, Maryland, located about 8.5 miles east-northeast of Oldtown. It was built by the Western Maryland Railway in 1906. Wikipedia

Mt. Lebanon Tunnel.label: Mt. Lebanon Tunnel
Mt. Lebanon Tunnel.description: The Mt. Lebanon Tunnel is a light rail tunnel in Allegheny County, Pennsylvania, also known as the Dormont/Mt. Lebanon Transit Tunnel, part of the Pittsburgh Light Rail system. Wikipedia

Natural Tunnel State Park.label: Natural Tunnel State Park
Natural Tunnel State Park.description: Natural Tunnel State Park is a Virginia state park, centered around the Natural Tunnel, a massive naturally formed cave that is so large it is used as a railroad tunnel. Wikipedia

Black Rock Tunnel.label: Black Rock Tunnel
Black Rock Tunnel.description: The Black Rock Tunnel is an active rail road tunnel of the old Reading Railroad. The 1835 tunnel was the Third rail tunnel constructed in the United States, and is the Third oldest still in use. Wikipedia

Turn Hole Tunnel.label: Turn Hole Tunnel
Turn Hole Tunnel.description: The Turn Hole Tunnel is an abandoned railroad tunnel near Jim Thorpe, Pennsylvania. Built by the Central Railroad of New Jersey, it carried part of that railroad's main line until 1912, and was used as ... Wikipedia

Quemahoning Tunnel.label: Quemahoning Tunnel
Quemahoning Tunnel.description: The Quemahoning Tunnel is a tunnel that was constructed by the New York Central Railroad for use on the stillborn South Pennsylvania Railroad. Wikipedia

Mount Washington Transit Tunnel.label: Mount Washington Transit Tunnel
Mount Washington Transit Tunnel.description: Mount Washington Transit Tunnel is an important public transportation link in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania, United States. Wikipedia

Koralm Tunnel.label: Koralm Tunnel
Koralm Tunnel.description:
The Koralm Tunnel is a railway tunnel that is under construction in Austria under the Koralpe mountain range. It is expected to be operational by 2022.
The tunnel will be 32.9 km long, which will make it Austria's longest railway tunnel. Wikipedia

Götatunneln.label: Götatunneln
Götatunneln.description:
The Götatunneln is a road tunnel under the inner city of Gothenburg in Sweden. It is 1,600 metres long.
Construction began 2000 and it was opened for traffic June 2006. The tunnel is separated in two tubes, each carrying three lanes of traffic. Wikipedia

Bramhope Tunnel.label: Bramhope Tunnel
Bramhope Tunnel.description: The Bramhope Tunnel is a railway tunnel 2.138 miles long, owned by Network Rail on a route currently operated mainly by Northern Rail. Wikipedia

Henryton Tunnel.label: Henryton Tunnel
Henryton Tunnel.description: The Henryton Tunnel, located near Henryton in southern Carroll County, Maryland, is the third-oldest tunnel in the world that remains in active railroad use. Wikipedia

Tanum Tunnel.label: Tanum Tunnel
Tanum Tunnel.description: Tanum Tunnel is 3,590-meter-long double-track railway tunnel on the Asker Line, between Jong in Bærum and Åstad in Asker, Norway. Wikipedia

Access to the Region's Core.label: Access to the Region's Core
Access to the Region's Core.description: Access to the Region's Core was a commuter rail project to increase passenger service capacity on New Jersey Transit between Secaucus Junction in New Jersey and Manhattan in New York City. Wikipedia

Carr's Tunnel.label: Carr's Tunnel
Carr's Tunnel.description: Carr's Tunnel is an abandoned railway tunnel in Greensburg, Pennsylvania. It was originally built in 1856 for the Pennsylvania Railroad. and brick lined 1868-1869. Wikipedia

Grafenort – Engelberg Tunnel.label: Grafenort – Engelberg Tunnel
Grafenort – Engelberg Tunnel.description: The Grafenort – Engelberg Tunnel is a railway tunnel built on the Luzern–Stans–Engelberg-Bahn, part of the Zentralbahn in Switzerland. Wikipedia

Lyttelton Rail Tunnel.label: Lyttelton Rail Tunnel
Lyttelton Rail Tunnel.description: The Lyttelton Rail Tunnel, initially called the Moorhouse Tunnel, links the city of Christchurch with the port of Lyttelton in the Canterbury region of New Zealand’s South Island. Wikipedia

Winston Tunnel.label: Winston Tunnel
Winston Tunnel.description:
The Winston Tunnel is a railroad tunnel located 9 miles west of Elizabeth, Illinois.
The tunnel was completed in 1888 for the Minnesota and Northwestern Railroad, a predecessor to the Chicago Great Western Railway. Wikipedia

Auburn Tunnel.label: Auburn Tunnel
Auburn Tunnel.description: Auburn Tunnel was a 19th century canal tunnel built for the Schuylkill Canal, near Auburn, Pennsylvania. Auburn Tunnel was the first transportation tunnel built in the United States. Wikipedia

Busk–Ivanhoe Tunnel.label: Busk–Ivanhoe Tunnel
Busk–Ivanhoe Tunnel.description: Busk–Ivanhoe Tunnel was a 9,394 ft long railroad tunnel at an elevation of 10,953 ft in Colorado. It was built by the Busk Tunnel Railway Company for the Colorado Midland Railroad in 1891 as a replacement ... Wikipedia

Cromer Tunnel.label: Cromer Tunnel
Cromer Tunnel.description: The Cromer Tunnel was built by the Norfolk and Suffolk Joint Railway to take their Cromer Beach to Mundesley line under the Great Eastern's Cromer High to Norwich line. Wikipedia

Penmanshiel Tunnel.label: Penmanshiel Tunnel
Penmanshiel Tunnel.description: Penmanshiel Tunnel is a now-disused railway tunnel near Grantshouse, Berwickshire, in the Scottish Borders region of Scotland. It was formerly part of the East Coast Main Line between Berwick-upon-Tweed and Dunbar. Wikipedia

Alva B. Adams Tunnel.label: Alva B. Adams Tunnel
Alva B. Adams Tunnel.description: The Alva B. Adams Tunnel is the principal component of the largest transmountain water project in Colorado--the Colorado-Big Thompson Project. Wikipedia

Gallitzin Tunnel.label: Gallitzin Tunnel
Gallitzin Tunnel.description: The Gallitzin Tunnels in Gallitzin, Pennsylvania, formed the Pennsylvania Railroad's passage through the Allegheny Mountains in western Pennsylvania. Wikipedia

Phoenixville Tunnel.label: Phoenixville Tunnel
Phoenixville Tunnel.description: The Phoenixville Tunnel, originally called the Fairview Tunnel, was part of the Pennsylvania Schuylkill Valley Railroad in Phoenixville, Pennsylvania. Wikipedia

Tanna Tunnel.label: Tanna Tunnel
Tanna Tunnel.description: Tanna Tunnel is a railroad tunnel in Shizuoka Prefecture, Japan operated by JR Central’s Tōkaidō Main Line. This 7.8 km long tunnel shortened the trunk route between Tokyo and Kobe by omitting a detour round the mountains between Atami and Numazu. Wikipedia

Bærum Tunnel.label: Bærum Tunnel
Bærum Tunnel.description: The Bærum Tunnel is a 5.5-kilometer long double track railway tunnel in Bærum, Norway. Running between Marstranderveien and Engervannet, it will make up most of the 6.7-kilometer long section of the ... Wikipedia

Belmont Tunnel (Nebraska).label: Belmont Tunnel
Belmont Tunnel (Nebraska).description: The Belmont Tunnel is a 698-foot long railway tunnel near the ghost town of Belmont about halfway between Crawford and Marsland, Nebraska, in western Dawes County. Wikipedia

Church Hill Tunnel.label: Church Hill Tunnel
Church Hill Tunnel.description: Church Hill Tunnel is an old Chesapeake and Ohio Railway tunnel extending for approximately 4,000 feet under the Church Hill section of Richmond, Virginia. Wikipedia

Combe Down Tunnel.label: Combe Down Tunnel
Combe Down Tunnel.description: Combe Down Tunnel is on the now-closed Somerset and Dorset Joint Railway main line, between Midford and Bath Queen Square, below high ground and the southern suburbs of Bath, England, emerging below the southern slopes of Combe Down village. Wikipedia

Great Northern Tunnel.label: Great Northern Tunnel
Great Northern Tunnel.description: The Great Northern Tunnel is a 1-mile double tracked railway tunnel under downtown Seattle, Washington, completed by the Great Northern Railway in 1905, and now owned by the BNSF Railway, on its Scenic Subdivision. Wikipedia

Hagerman Tunnel.label: Hagerman Tunnel
Hagerman Tunnel.description:
Hagerman Tunnel was a 2,161 ft railroad tunnel crossing the Continental Divide in Colorado at an altitude of 11,528 ft.
Constructed in 1887 by the Colorado Midland Railroad and named for Midland officer ... Wikipedia

Kaimai Tunnel.label: Kaimai Tunnel
Kaimai Tunnel.description: The Kaimai Tunnel is a railway tunnel through the Kaimai Range in the North Island of New Zealand. Since it was opened in 1978, it has held the title of longest tunnel, at 8.879 kilometres, in New ... Wikipedia

North River Tunnels.label: North River Tunnels
North River Tunnels.description: The North River Tunnels carry Amtrak and New Jersey Transit rail lines under the Hudson River between Weehawken, New Jersey and Pennsylvania Station in Manhattan, New York City. Wikipedia

Saltash Tunnel.label: Saltash Tunnel
Saltash Tunnel.description:
The Saltash Tunnel is a road tunnel on the A38 at Saltash in Cornwall, UK and was opened in 1988.
The central lane operates as a reversible lane to cope with holiday and rush hour traffic and the speed limit is 30 mph. Wikipedia

Ulriken Tunnel.label: Ulriken Tunnel
Ulriken Tunnel.description: Ulriken Tunnel is a railway tunnel on the Bergen Line between Bergen Station and Arna Station in Norway. The 7,670-meter long tunnel runs under the northern part of the mountain Ulriken in Bergen. Wikipedia

Virginia Avenue Tunnel.label: Virginia Avenue Tunnel
Virginia Avenue Tunnel.description: The Virginia Avenue Tunnel is a railroad tunnel in Washington, D.C. owned by CSX Transportation. It is part of the CSX RF&P Subdivision and serves freight trains along the eastern seaboard routes, providing a bypass around Union Station. Wikipedia

Downtown Hudson Tubes.label: Downtown Hudson Tubes
Downtown Hudson Tubes.description: The Downtown Hudson Tubes are a pair of tunnels that carry PATH trains under the Hudson River between New York City and Jersey City in the United States. In lower Manhattan the trains travel to and from the World Trade Center station. Wikipedia

Whitrope Tunnel.label: Whitrope Tunnel
Whitrope Tunnel.description:
The Whitrope Tunnel is a disused railway tunnel in the Scottish Borders, situated 12 miles south of Hawick on the Waverley Route, just close to Whitrope. With a length of 1,208 yards in length.
It is the fourth longest tunnel in Scotland. Wikipedia

Burdale Tunnel.label: Burdale Tunnel
Burdale Tunnel.description: Burdale Tunnel is a railway tunnel on the now abandoned Malton & Driffield Railway. It lies near the village of Burdale in North Yorkshire, England, between the former Burdale and Wharram railway ... Wikipedia
